          <h2 class="featurette-heading">Our Origin</h2>
          <p class="lead">George J. ROderer Sr. was born in the foothills of the Alps in the small village of Fichtelberg, Germany in the year 1872. He learned the skill of shoemaking as an apprentice to the village shoemaker. In 1892, his widowed mother brought her family of four to Dayton, Ohio, where a core of friends and neighbors from Fichtelberg had already established themselves.</p>
          <p class="lead">George initially worked as a toolmaker at the National Cash Register Company, but continued to use his shoemaking skills, repairing the shoes of his fellow workers. In 1906, he began to purchase and resell footwear from his Xenia Avenue home.</p>
          <p class="lead"></p>
          <p class="lead"></p>

        </div>
