          <h2 class="featurette-heading">His Family and His Business Grew</h2>
          <p class="lead">In 1913, the year of the great Dayton flood, he began construction of a new home and store in Xenia Avenue, just two blocks west of the original location. He sold his original home to his brother, Johh B. Sr., who, ercouraged by the steram of people arriving at his front door seeking new shoes, opened the first J.B. Roderer shoes. Their neighbors knew them as big Roderer and little Roderer.</p>
        </div>
                <div class="col-md-5">
         <%= image_tag('roderer_store_bw.jpg', :alt => "Roderer Store b&w") %>
        </div>
      </div>
